UPDATED: OCT 19, 2015 Hazy amber/straw color. Big mango on the nose but otherwise mild for a citra single hop.. Palate is great. Drinkability is high here but its rather mild hop-wise with little bitterness - I usually never want too much bitterness. Here I could use some. Pretty orangy or kumquatty too.. Great pale ale none the less. #IOWA represent!
Had this a few times over the last week and its growing on me. I feel I should at least pump the score up to a straight 4. 
@motherhrother shared this with me on my first go. Thanks player!
